As 2018 draws to a close, The Chronicle looks back on the stories that shaped life at the University during the last twelve months.
Racially charged incidents strike campusSince the beginning of 2018, many racially charged incidents have been reported on campus.
In mid-October, a student reported finding a swastika carved into the stall door in a bathroom in the Languages Building.
Duke Electric Vehicles sets world recordA team of Duke students spent their summer breaking a Guinness World Record.
Additionally, Ben Reese, vice president for institutional equity, announced that he would step down at the end of the 2018-2019 academic year.